<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Expose" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Expose,</orth> 1) to cast out to chance: <cit><quote>to e. the child,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 78</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to give up, to leave to the mercy of; followed by <cit><quote>to:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 3, 71</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.2.106" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 2, 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.3.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 3, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.70" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 5, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.230" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 230</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.4.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 4, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.164" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 164</bibl>. By <emph>into</emph> instead of <emph>unto</emph>: <cit><quote>--d myself into the danger of this town,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 5.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 86</bibl></cit>. By <emph>against</emph>: <cit><quote>to be --d against the warring winds,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.7.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 7, 32</bibl></cit> (Ff and M. Edd. <emph>opposed</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>